bc-vigil (0.1.3-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Fix scans permanently failing with "malformed left digest file"
    once an empty target was scanned: 0.1.1 synthesized a summary-only
    digest for empty targets, but bc-hash diff rejects that format,
    which broke every subsequent scheduled scan whose baseline was the
    synth file. run_hash no longer synthesizes; empty scans are stored
    with digest_path=NULL, and a baseline that is empty or unusable is
    automatically replaced by the first real scan (self-heal for prod
    DBs already poisoned by 0.1.1).

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Sun, 19 Apr 2026 09:34:35 +0000

bc-vigil (0.1.2-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Fix schedule form silently ignoring the time picked by the user:
    the template rendered two inputs named "time" (one per mode panel
    plus a global hidden fallback at 03:00). Weekly/monthly panels
    only updated the first match via JS, while the hidden one shipped
    with its default value to the server. Each mode panel now owns a
    single visible name="time" input, panels are disabled by JS when
    unused, no hidden fallback, no onchange glue.

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Sat, 18 Apr 2026 21:00:00 +0000

bc-vigil (0.1.1-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Fix "unexpected: No such file" when scanning an empty target:
    bc-hash exits 0 without producing a digest, run_hash now synthesizes
    an empty-summary digest so the baseline/diff flow stays valid.
  * systemd unit: grant AmbientCapabilities=CAP_DAC_READ_SEARCH so the
    unprivileged bc-vigil user can read /etc/shadow, SSH host keys,
    /etc/ufw/*, etc. Read-only capability, no write privilege added.

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Sat, 18 Apr 2026 20:30:00 +0000

bc-vigil (0.1.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Initial release.
  * Web frontend for bc-hash with targets, schedules, scan drift detection.
  * Storage module (disk usage via psutil).
  * FR/EN i18n.
  * DB backup/restore/reset.
  * 100% test coverage.

